FILE PERMISSIONS :

    LIST DETAILS : ls -l /Path/To/File_OR_Folder

    EACH 3 BITS FOR USER GROUP OTHERS : 
        READABLE : r
        WRITABLE : w
        EXECUTABLE : x
        NONE  : -


MODIFY PERMISSIONS : 

    ADD PERMISSION TO FILE FOR USER  : chmod u+x Filename

    REMOVE PERMISSION FROM FILE FOR GROUP : chmod g-x Filename

    EACH NUMBER FOR USER GROUP OTHER : chmod 777 Filename
        READABLE : 4
        WRITABLE : 2
        EXECUTABLE : 1
        NONE  : 0


OWNERSHIP PERMISSIONS : 

    MODIFY USER OWNERSHIP : sudo chown NewOwner_USername Filename

    MODIFY GROUP OWNERSHIP : sudo chgrp NewGroupName Filename

    MODIFY BOTH : sudo chown NewOwner_USername:NewGroupName Filename


UMASK : 

    CHANGE DEFAULT PERMISSION FOR FILE CREATION : umask 021 {all permissions except 021 will be given}

    
SET USER OR GROUP ID : 

    GIVE SUID TO USER : sudo chmod u+s Filename
        EXECUTABLE : s
        NON EXECUTABLE : S

    GIVE SGID TO GROUP : sudo chmod g+s Filename












